text: Cozy little authentic korean eatery! Concise menu but everything is a knockout! The ramyun was cooked with love and so satisfying to eat, and the gimbap was so fresh and generous! Will definitely come back.

One of my favourite Korean restaurants. Reasonable prices for delightful dishes, and the kimbap is freshly made. All the dishes are homemade and the food is absolutely amazing. The kimchi fried rice is also very tasty. Definitely recommend this restaurant!

Authentic Korean food with delicious kimbap! They offer set meals for lunch and dinner, perfect for dine-in or takeout. All dishes are tasty, and the freshly made kimchi is a standout. Will always support this place!

When I asked May why she opened a cafe she said, "I just want to keep doing something I love for as long as I can." May's makes the most heart-warming, flavorful, hit-the-spot food you have ever tasted. Her kimchi fried rice and gimbap are unmatched. She also has a special dish each week so please follow her on Instagram! You can even place large orders through social media or WhatsApp.

The location is green, comfortable, and quiet. You can grab a coffee around the corner after you are done. May's smile is just as warm as her food! This is a most welcome spot in this neighborhood, please try for yourself!
